elosi A</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2010-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>1571-0645</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/7FFC0907-ADDF-4BEB-BD9F-A66C6D6A5E05"><gtr:id>7FFC0907-ADDF-4BEB-BD9F-A66C6D6A5E05</gtr:id><gtr:title>The mechanics of embodiment: a dialog on embodiment and computational modeling.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Frontiers in psychology</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/d93971f4f21570d991792849625dc7ea"><gtr:id>d93971f4f21570d991792849625dc7ea</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Pezzulo G</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2011-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>1664-1078</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/01802B83-7F1E-41F1-8E8B-7D9D54CA64E4"><gtr:id>01802B83-7F1E-41F1-8E8B-7D9D54CA64E4</gtr:id><gtr:title>Object affordance influences instruction span.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Experimental brain research</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/8f886dbadbfc52d5c4f04ac77bfa625f"><gtr:id>8f886dbadbfc52d5c4f04ac77bfa625f</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Apel JK</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2012-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0014-4819</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/18E40AC6-F9F9-4FE7-8501-55AA59ACF773"><gtr:id>18E40AC6-F9F9-4FE7-8501-55AA59ACF773</gtr:id><gtr:title>Attention deployment during memorizing and executing complex instructions.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Experimental brain research</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/8f886dbadbfc52d5c4f04ac77bfa625f"><gtr:id>8f886dbadbfc52d5c4f04ac77bfa625f</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Apel JK</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2011-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0014-4819</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://